    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3040212568" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3040212568" />
    <a title="Raul Bimenyimana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43664238-raul-bimenyimana"><img alt="Raul Bimenyimana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1466510542p2/43664238.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3040212568?book_show_action=true">Nov 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Raul Bimenyimana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Raul Bimenyimana" href="/user/show/43664238-raul-bimenyimana">Raul Bimenyimana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43664238-raul-bimenyimana?shelf=women-writers">women-writers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3040212568" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3863484630466559539">The title of the book sums up what this story is about, a housekeeper who is employed to take care of a cottage belonging to a mathematics professor who, because of an accident, has a memory that lasts eighty minutes, and the housekeeper&apos;s son named root by the professor, because the shape of his head resembles that of a square root. While doing her work, the housekeeper and her son develop a strong friendship with the professor and are connected to each other by, you guessed it - mathematics - </span>
  <span id="freeText3863484630466559539" style="display:none">The title of the book sums up what this story is about, a housekeeper who is employed to take care of a cottage belonging to a mathematics professor who, because of an accident, has a memory that lasts eighty minutes, and the housekeeper's son named root by the professor, because the shape of his head resembles that of a square root. While doing her work, the housekeeper and her son develop a strong friendship with the professor and are connected to each other by, you guessed it - mathematics - and baseball.<br /><br />On the surface, this sounds like a boring story and while reading you expect "something" to happen, an event that is cataclysmic, that would push the story, but the event never really arrives, not the way I'd expect it to at least, yet the story still moves, entrancing till the end. This is a quiet book, wonderfully written, about human connections, friendship, and the beauty of numbers and sometimes it is just the kind of book you need to read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3863484630466559539" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


